It's Paul -- again.  I'll throw another one out there for discussion.  There has been news in the paper recently about the ban of the use of land mines.  It doesn't look, at the present (last I heard) that we (U.S.) would support the ban.<br><br>
I gave this a little thought.  My first thought was to agree and that we do whatever is best to win and for our troops.<br><br>
My second thought was no.  I recall the booby traps, etc. around the Cu Chi area and remember well being choppered out of an area that was heavily &quot;mined&quot; with our duds and all.<br><br>
The long term results on future generations was the final factor in making my choice.<br><br>
What do you guys think?<br><br>
